<p>

A <b>warehouseman</b> can be someone who works in a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../146/549146.xml">
warehouse</link>, usually delivering goods for sale or storage, or, in older usage, someone who owns a warehouse and sells goods directly from it or from a shop fronting onto the warehouse (similar to a modern <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../824/55824.xml">
Cash and carry</link>)<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref>. </p>
<p>

An <it>Italian warehouseman</it> was someone who stocked goods from <system wordnetid="108435388" confidence="0.8">
<economy wordnetid="108366753" confidence="0.8">
<group wordnetid="100031264" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../532/14532.xml">
Italy</link></group>
</economy>
</system>
 such as <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../871/23871.xml">
pasta</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../551/18582551.xml">
pickle</link>s, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../581/98581.xml">
perfume</link>s, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../843/10843.xml">
fruit</link>s, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../776/23776.xml">
paint</link>s and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../598/49598.xml">
pigment</link>s (they were often known as Oil and Italian warehouseman or Oilman and Italian warehouseman to highlight the selling of oil products) <ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref>.</p>
<p>

A <it>Manchester warehouseman</it> was a wholesaler of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../212/56212.xml">
linen</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../892/51892.xml">
cloth</link> made in the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../263/6837263.xml">
factories surrounding</link> <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../206/20206.xml">
Manchester</link></village>
 in the North-West of <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../316/9316.xml">
England</link></country>
<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%223%22])">3</ref>.</p>

